node.text:
Being away from home, but most of all not know when I will be able to go, make me miss Sweden more than ever before. To make the wait easier I found an online store in the UK specialising on Scandinavian treats (scandikitchen.co.uk). Obviously it won’t make me miss my family any less, which is the main reason why I want to go home. But I thought it be fun and filled my basked with all my favourite Swedish treats, and had Tomas try them, both to eat and to pronounce them 😂

ps I added texts for you to try and pronounce them too. Comment a 🇸🇪 if you have ever been to Sweden or if it’s on your bucket list x

#sweden #scandinavia #bortabramenhemmabäst #homesick #hemlängtan #pilotmaria

node.text:
I know flying in “bad” weather can be terrifying, especially for you scared of flying. During February storm after storm hit Europe and I received several DMs asking ‘Can the airplane really take off and land in this wind?’ Ask the Pilot:
Every airplane type has a maximum certified wind that we can take. If the wind would be above our limits we would not make an attempt to land, we would never do anything jeopardising the safety onboard!

In aviation fuel = time! We always carry enough extra fuel with us to divert to an alternate airport if so would be needed. In addition when the forecasted weather is pushing the limits, we take even more fuel with us! Enough fuel so that we comfortable can make an approach, a go around, fuel for a second approach if the weather was getting better, holding fuel and fuel to cover for an alternate where the weather is forecasted to be better.

Hope this answer some of your questions, if not feel free to ask them below, I’m more than happy to help best I can.

I will also dedicate this weeks ‘Ask the Pilot’ (Pilot related video I release every week on my YouTube channel, YouTube.com/pilotmaria) to the topic so feel free to ask any questions your have regarding weather and flying below.

Apologies for the quality, when I’m at work I’m at work and my fully attention goes to that, for that reason I only have my phone and iPad to create short clips when time permitting.

Hey just being honest over here, it’s not easy to park a big pickup truck 😂 But I’m getting there 😉

As airline crew you don’t always get to celebrate the festive holidays with your family. This year I was scheduled to work on the 24th and 26th leaving me no option but to stay in England while my family celebrated back in Sweden (and Tomas in Portugal). Little did I know just how magical this Christmas would become to be 🎄

One of my best friends (I believe that one can have many, many best friends 💛) @emiliepix is a flight attendant for American Airlines and happen to be that she had a trip Los Angeles to London with a 24 hour (ish) layover in London! So I picked her up at Heathrow and we made a delicious Christmas dinner and exchanged gifts, and ps Pumpkin absolutely adored Emilie! I’m so fortunate to have such amazing friends!

With a Christmas Spirit filled heart I look forward to New Years Eve and all 2020 got planned for me ✨✨ #christmas #christmas2019 #christmasday #bestfriends #pilotmaria #airlinecrew #crewlife #vlog #christmasspirit #igtv #fortunate #squadgoals #girlboss #crew #merrychristmas

I often get asked what it’s like for me as a pilot to fly as a passenger? Do pilots judge other pilots landings?

I absolutely LOVE to be a passenger, sit back relax and enjoy the view (although I do very much prefer the view from flightdeck, but this will also do 😉) I was invited to @thepointsguy #TPGawards in NYC and one thing you can count on is that when @briankelly invites you to an event, he make sure to get you there ‘in point style’👌Here are some clips I was originally planning on sharing in stories, but as I wasn’t connected to the WiFi I never ended up sharing them. Still a pretty spectacular view I felt was too pretty to stay unshared on my camera roll.

It was my first time flying with @virginatlantic and oh lord that chocolate lava cake on its own would be worth another flight around the world!! Learn how to get your upgrade and fly in business on @thepointsguy Background music from @epidemicsound Shot on iPhone #backtobasics

node.text:
737-8200 familiarisation training, complete ☑️ and I’m now allowed to fly our newest member in the fleet.

Today was a great training day. It wasn’t graded like most of our simulator sessions usually are. Instead it allowed for a more relaxed session, just the way I prefer it and it was interesting to learn more about the aircraft and it’s new systems and layout.

Ps as a pilot you will never stop studying, keep that in mind when making your career choice 😉🙃

node.text:
Who else is a ‘prepare everything the night before’ kind of person?

The alarm is set for 03:30 am and I have my first flight! Excited, yet an odd feeling to go back to the somewhat “normal”

I’m used to spend all day with Alice. I’ve never left her to go to work, I’ve never really been without her at all to be honest, except for the simulator training days that I had. It will be a strange feeling to go back to working a schedule. But I know Tomas is excited to cut down on his hours so that he can spend more time with Alice too.

Walton on the maze beach day. Alice’s first beach day. It was almost thirty degrees back home but only an hour away it had decreased to 23 degrees and a generous breeze.

node.text:
Alice’s first beach day!

So far learned that we need: Water proof beach blanket (especially on a beach like Walton-on-the-Naze that is tide dependent) and a beach tent, so that I don’t need to act shade protector for Alice.

Ps I have my first flight tomorrow! Flying to Spain and back. On this first flight I will sit as an observer to learn all new procedures that have changed over the past year.
